<html>
<head>
<!-- $Id$ -->
<title>GridShib CA</title>
</head>
@HTML_HEADER@
<table width=100% cellpadding=5>
<tr><td><p><p><p></td></tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#30A030" align=center><b>About</b></td>
<td colspan=2>
This is the GridShib-CA (version @PACKAGE_VERSION_STRING@). This software
allows you to acquire a short-lived (<1 day) Grid Credential through
your web browser and Shibboleth. After successfully authenticating, a
credential will be installed and is suitable for use with Grid Tools
such as GT4.
<p>
Note that as with all Grid credentials this GridShib CA must be
trusted by any resources you use and the identity from the Credentials
(aka the Distinguished Name or DN) must be authorized (in the
grid-mapfile).
<p>
For further documentation and the latest release please see 
<a href="http://gridshib.globus.org">http://gridshib.globus.org</a>.
Full documentation regarding this release can be found at
<a href="http://gridshib.globus.org/docs/@DOC_INSTALL_DIR@">
http://gridshib.globus.org/docs/@DOC_INSTALL_DIR@</a>

</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><p><p><p></td></tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#A0A0A0" align=center><b>Prerequisites</b></td>
<td>
Prior to using the GridShib CA on a new client system,
please <a href="checkPrerequisites.html">make sure you have the client
system properly configured</a>. Failing to do so may cause you
headaches as well as being insecure.
<p>
The GridShib-CA will work for for any Institution with a Shibboleth
server in InQueue that will release an identity to the
GridShib-CA. You can find the list of institutions that are part of 
InQueue <a href="http://inqueue.internet2.edu/who/">here</a>.
<p>
If your institution doesn't have a Shibboleth Identity
provider <a href="http://inqueue.internet2.edu/who/">in InQueue</a>
<!-- or
<a href="http://www.incommonfederation.org/participants.cfm">in
InCommon</a>
--> (or it doesn't release your identity to us), we suggest you
register with a public identity provider such
as <a href="http://www.openidp.org">OpenIdp</a> or
<a href="http://www.protectnetwork.com">ProtectNetwork</a>, both of
which are easy to use and known to work with the GridShib-CA.
</td>
<td align=center>
<a href="http://www.openidp.org">
<img src="openidp-logo-small.png" Align="middle"></a>
<a href="http://www.protectnetwork.com">
<img src="protectnetwork.png" Align="middle"></a>
</td>
</tr>
<tr><td><p><p><p></td></tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#0303C0" rowspan=2 align=center><b>Go</b></td>
<td colspan=2 align=center>
<table width=100%>
<tr><td width=50% align=center>
<!--
<b>Login via a Federation</b>
-->
<br>
<form action="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@/Shibboleth.sso/WAYF/InQueue">
<input type="hidden" name="target"
			 value="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@@SHIB_PROTECTED_CGI_BIN_URL@/login.cgi">
<input type="submit" value="Login via InQueue">
</form>
<!--
		The GridShib-CA isn't in InCommon yet
<form action="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@/Shibboleth.sso/WAYF/InCommon">
<input type="hidden" name="target"
			 value="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@@SHIB_PROTECTED_CGI_BIN_URL@/login.cgi">
<input type="submit" value="Login via InCommon">
</form>
-->
</td>
<td align=center>
<b>Login via a Public Identity Provider</b>
<form action="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@/Shibboleth.sso/WAYF/InQueue">
<input type="hidden" name="target"
			 value="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@@SHIB_PROTECTED_CGI_BIN_URL@/login.cgi">
<input type="hidden" name="providerId"
			 value="urn:mace:inqueue:openidp.org">
<input type="submit" value="Login via OpenIdp">
</form>

<form action="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@/Shibboleth.sso/WAYF/InCommon">
<input type="hidden" name="target"
			 value="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@@SHIB_PROTECTED_CGI_BIN_URL@/login.cgi">
<input type="hidden" name="providerId"
			 value="https://idp.protectnetwork.org/protectnetwork-idp">
<input type="submit" value="Login via ProtectNetwork">
</form>
</td><tr>
<tr><td colspan=2 align=center>
<!--
		This assumes you have a myVocs session established in your
		Shibboleth configuration.
 -->
<b>Login via Other Mechanisms</b>
<form action="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@/Shibboleth.sso/WAYF/myvocs">
<input type="hidden" name="target"
			 value="https://@WWW_HOSTNAME@@SHIB_PROTECTED_CGI_BIN_URL@/login.cgi">
<input type="submit" value="Login via myVocs">
</form>
</td></tr>
</table>
</td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2>
After clicking on a link you will then be redirected back to that
site to authenticate and then you will be returned to the GridShib CA.
If you have any problems, please send email
to <a href="mailto:gridshib-users@globus.org">gridshib-users@globus.org</a>
</td></tr>
</table>
@HTML_FOOTER@
</html>
